On the PR page, if you click the "Open Tasks" link, you should be able to get redirected to the task that you&#x27;ve clicked. If you follow the steps to reproduce below, however, the screen will simply flash and do nothing instead of redirecting you to the correct task.

*Steps to reproduce*

# Open a PR with a task in it;
# The "Open tasks" link should appear on the right corner of the PR screen. Click on it, and click on the "chain" icon to get redirected to the task. You should get redirected to the correct task;
# Scroll up on the page and click on either the "Commits" or "Activity" tab;
# Go back to the "Overview" tab;
# Follow the same steps as BCLOUD-2, and you should see the screen flashing and doing nothing instead of redirecting the user to the correct task.

Running the below API adds a new deploy key (or Access key) in a repo, however, it prints an error.

{code}
#!curl
curl -X POST \
-H "Authorization: Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN" \
-H "Content-type: application/json" \
https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/username/repo_name/deploy-keys -d \
&#x27;{
    "key": "ssh-rsa PUBLIC_SSH_KEY_HERE",
    "label": "mydeploykey"
}&#x27;

{code}

*Error Response*:

{code}
#!curl
{"type": "error", "error": {"message": "Something went wrong", "id": "a08995dc96164399a5834cddc77197e2"}}
{code}

h3. Expected Result
There should not be an error because the public SSH key was successfully added.

h3. Actual Result
There is an error response even if the public SSH key was successfully added.

h3. Workaround
Make sure the repository name does not contains the character "/" or forward-slash.

We are seeing issues creating webhooks with Bitbucket due to what appears to be a recent change in API response. There have been no known changes from our end and this functionality seems to be broken as of 4/12.

Existing webhooks are not affected. However, new webhook registration is returning very different response payload causing the integration to fail.

